{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_62","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented US-006 with a unified CLI error envelope and committed it.\n\nCommit:\n`0ade5fc`  \n`feat: US-006 - Unified error handling and user messages`\n\nWhat was done:\n- Added unified error envelope at CLI layer with required categories: `policy`, `auth`, `transport`, `state`, `validation`.\n- Added per-error correlation ID generation and output.\n- Added correlation context fields in output (`session_id`, `provider`) and context extraction from error chains.\n- Mapped typed crate errors (`WireError`, `AppError`) plus fallback string classification into user-friendly messages.\n- Added required guidance:\n  - transport/network errors suggest checking connectivity\n  - auth errors suggest checking API key config\n  - missing provider/config points to `./config.example.toml`\n- Sanitized provider/remote errors so raw upstream details are not leaked.\n- Switched main/agent/repl error printing to use the unified envelope.\n- Removed bootstrap string-wrapping in command paths to preserve typed error mapping.\n- Added/updated tests for category mapping, labels, context/correlation presence, config hint, and sanitization.\n\nQuality checks run and passing:\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo test --workspace`\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}}
